choices.text: You have a string of decimal digits s. Let's define b_{ij} = s_{i} s_{j}. Find in matrix b the number of such rectangles that the sum b_{ij} for all cells (i, j) that are the elements of the rectangle equals a in each rectangle. A rectangle in a matrix is a group of four integers (x, y, z, t) (x   y, z   t). The elements of the rectangle are all cells (i, j) such that x   i   y, z   j   t.
